CNCP v1 26089
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12843: When using JSX to render a slot in a selected loop, the children of slots.default always output the last Element.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:18.098622+00:00",
  "text": "When using JSX to render a slot in a selected loop, the children of slots.default always output the last Element.\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/447824cd-a0e7-41c5-a2d0-dd22084aeb42)\n\nAfter looping three times, the elements in the children of slots.default all point to the last one.\n\nWhen the Vue version is 3.4+, it outputs correctly, but all versions of 3.5 have this issue.  （like this: https://play.vuejs.org/# ）\n\nI also found that when the input is text or a basic element like span, div, etc., as long as their content and attributes are exactly the same, this issue also occurs. (like this: https://play.vuejs.org/#)\n\nHowever, if I add attributes like key or others, it outputs correctly.\n\n\nCould this be due to Vue 3.5 optimizations related to the virtual DOM?\n\n### What is expected?\n\nWhen looping, the corresponding tag can be correctly accessed through slots.default.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe children of slots.default always output the last element of the loop.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "has workaround",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
